YOUR WAIT IS OVER!! 

We *The Writers and Poets Club of CBIT* holding an objective to reflect the Impact of Institutional Innovations and Contribution to Technological Progress through writings and poetry. We are one of the young but zestful and unique clubs of CBIT. We believe in wiping off the borders of Region, Religion, Cast, Creed and Gender among the students and make them collectively contribute to the nation. 

*So let's get our pens together and work together!!* 

*Yes! The Writers And Poets CLUB are recruiting!!* 

I don't come to every room,
Neither do I lie,

I came to this room today,
So mixed up, to find someone with a lion's share,

If there is a lion in you,
Then why not show the world,

You must be writing a lot,
But what Lion is he, who is mystery to the world.
                 ~M.Adnan 
      (Administrative head)

30/01/2021, 12:36 - Puneeth CBIT: Hello everyone! 

The theme for SUDHEE-2021 is decided as *" Digital Innovations in 21st Century"* . Those interested can participate in the poster design competition for sudhee. The theme of the Sudhee-2021should reflect aptly and significantly in poster design. This time, teams are allowed as well for the competition with a maximum of 2 students per team. So form your team, and get into designing! 
The winners will be awarded with cash prize and certificates and their poster design will be used for Sudhee 2021. 
Make sure you use the attached cbit banner on the poster. Submit your posters to sudhee2021@cbit.ac.in by 5-02-2021.
30/01/2021, 12:36 - Puneeth CBIT: Hello everyone! 

The theme for SUDHEE-2021 is decided as *" Digital Innovations in 21st Century"* . Those interested can participate in the poster design competition for sudhee. The theme of the Sudhee-2021should reflect aptly and significantly in poster design. This time, teams are allowed as well for the competition with a maximum of 2 students per team. So form your team, and get into designing! 
The winners will be awarded with cash prize and certificates and their poster design will be used for Sudhee 2021. 
Make sure you use the attached cbit banner on the poster. Submit your posters to sudhee2021@cbit.ac.in by 5-02-2021.

A new collaboration with Unerased Poetry

Ever wished you could venture into your mind-
And bring out all ideas and thoughts of every kind

All we ask is your will, and a little of your time

25/02/2021, 15:35 - +91 90146 06623: Tech virus has 3 rounds:
Round 1: Tell me 5- In this round, the participants will be divided into groups and asked questions. The participants should name any 5 words related to the question.
Round 2: Word Chain- It is similar to what we call word building, i.e., come up with a new word based on the last word's last letter. The participants will be divided into groups and will have to play the game only with technical terms. If participants cannot answer 3 times, they're out of the game.
Round 3: Jumbled Pattern- The code for a series or pattern is provided with a few lines jumbled. The participants have to rearrange them to get the correct output.
Prizes:
Winner-1000
Runner 1-600
Runner 2-400
Contact Numbers:
Srija Chitkesi- 9515206880
Sreeja Palla-9381466075

window=Tk()
window.geometry("250x250")
window.title("calculator")
def btn_click(item):
    global exp
    exp=exp+str(item)
    print(exp)
    input_text.set(exp)
exp=""
input_text=StringVar()
def bt_equal():
    global exp
    result=str(eval(exp))
    input_text.set(result)
    exp=""
one=Button(window,text="1",fg="blue",height=3,width=10,command=lambda:btn_click(1)).grid(row=1,column=1)
two=Button(window,text="2",fg="blue",height=3,width=10,command=lambda:btn_click(2)).grid(row=2,column=1)
multiply=Button(window,text="*",fg="blue",height=3,width=10,command=lambda:btn_click("*")).grid(row=1,column=3)
input_field=Entry(window,textvariable=input_text,width=50)
input_field.grid(row=2,column=2)
equal=Button(window,text="=",width=10,height=3,command=bt_equal).grid(row=4,column=3)
window.mainloop()

16/07/2021, 19:52 - +91 80744 57475: Dear Friends and Colleagues,

Greetings from Swecha! We hope that you and your family are safe and
healthy. We are glad to write this mail to inform you about the upcoming
"Industry oriented Remote Training and
Internship 2021" that is being conducted with a focused theme, "Let's
fight the Covid Pandemic Together!".

Swecha is a non-profit organization working towards spreading Free (as
in freedom) Software and bridging the digital divide. Swecha organizes
Internships,
Workshops and Camps to spread knowledge and the use of free software
that benefits the community at large.

The Projects and the initiatives that Swecha takes up have the potential
to benefit the community. Projects ranging from building People's health
infrastructure, a sophisticated community-driven public health
infrastructure to building BalaSwecha OS and integrated conferencing
systems have aimed at bridge the digital divide, involving the
collective contributions from the community. The workflow mechanism of
these projects has been meticulously collaborated with the community and
incorporated the industry methods of SDLC (Software Development Life
Cycles), such as Agile methodologies. As a mentor for this Internship,
you would be involved in guiding the projects with your expertise on
SDLCs, MLOps, Kubernetes, etc.  Your experience in the industry /
academia will help engineering students by inculcating industry
practices, strengthening team work and encouraging leadership. Also,
this opportunity enables you to be part of the collectives in building
the larger projects that benefit the larger community and carry out the
experience in your local groups.

During the Internship, you will be required to spend a minimum of 3-4
Hrs per week mentoring the project, which involves your participation in
project discussions.
Our Flag Ship Projects:
* People's Health (https://peopleshealth.in), Peoples Mart, Speech
* Recognition & Dialog System (https://voice.swecha.org), Free Software
* Conferencing & Streaming (https://virtual.swecha.org), Swecha Os,
* BalaSwecha OS, GAFAM FireWall, Swecha CRM & Event Management Software
and many more.

In this regard, we would like to invite you to sign-up for mentoring in
this "Industry Oriented Remote Training and Internship" program and
"Let's fight the Covid Pandemic Together!".

Our Internship starts from August 1st.

Registration Here: https://swecha.org/internship2021
Amount: Early bird fee: Rs.1000/-
         Internship fee: Rs.1300/-

Thank you!

30/08/2021, 21:06 - Shabaz CBIT: <Media omitted>
30/08/2021, 21:06 - Shabaz CBIT: What is an International Model United Nations (IMUN)
conference and Why should someone participate in it ?

International MUN online conference is a 2-day model UN conference
where participants from around the world present solutions to global
issues. They can choose topics of their choices in every conference. In
a 2-day conference, they research about the topics, debate, network
with other participants from different countries etc.

Participants also get study materials, "free MUN training sessions",
"experts QnA and position paper submissions". At the end of the
conference, all participants receive participation certificates
recognised by the Australian embassy and the United Nations. The
best participants receive two certificates, one is participation
certificate and another is award certificate.

For more info. Can DM me at Instagram
varun_kamshetty

12/11/2021, 06:41 - Nikhitha CBIT: Bright day everyone!
As team team Communicando gears up for *Speech Relay* this Sunday(3pm-5pm, online), we have received a lot of queries about what and how the event will be and why should you be registering for it?
*Here's the link*: https://bit.ly/SpeechRelay
So, here are all your questions answered:
*WHAT IS IT?*
This is *not* a speech giving or debating competition. The term 'speech' in the name symbolises speaking in general. Actually, this is *the board game of 21st century*. Here participants will be teamed up randomly and will be competing based on their spontaneity, wit, enthusiasm and love for something new. Once the players start the game they'll be speaking about various things, guessing, playing, tricking and a lot moree ‚ú®
12/11/2021, 06:41 - Nikhitha CBIT: Speaking can be of many kinds, right?
But what usual competitions do is, they make it so monotonous that there's no fun left. We tried to take this one level up and include elements like no other game ever has. 
*WHO CAN TAKE PART?*
Everyone. No age limit, no college restrictions.
Anyone who wants have fun on Sunday, is welcomed with open arms. 
And the biggest question of all,
*WHY SHOULD WE TAKE PART?*
1.Every participant will get an *E-certificate* of participation which can be used to gain activity points for the semester.
2.You will get to meet a lot of people and build your network, probably the co-founder of your startup will be your teammate here.
3.*Each member of the winning team will get an Amazon Kindle Subscription for 1 month!!*

11/12/2021, 21:16 - Dhruv CBIT: The NEO Educational Foundation presents to you 
*The 5th National Engineering Olympiad*!

The National Engineering Olympiad is a competitive platform for the engineering students to showcase your aptitude skills and represent yourself at the national level.

Register now!
https://nationalolympiad.org/?refid=325521112

*The Rounds:*
Similar to the previous four editions of the National Engineering Olympiad, the exam will be conducted in two rounds.

Round 1: Basic Aptitude Test- 60 mins, 60 questions. 
Dates are 18th & 19th December 2021. 
Round 2: Technical Ability Test- Online MCQ Exam based on your syllabus of the year & branch you are studying in. 

*Please Note:*
Both rounds are to be attempted _online_ from your home!

*The Rewards:* 

_For the top performers:_
-Top 10 of each year & branch will be awarded a Medal of Excellence.
-Top 30 of each year & branch will be awarded a Certificate of Excellence.

_For all participants:_
-Guaranteed Internships in various domains.
-A national-level participation certificate.
-Career-oriented webinars by experts for free.

(More details are available on the website)

Hurry up! Last day to register for Phase 3 is 17th December.
Visit https://nationalolympiad.org/?refid=325521112

05/01/2022, 14:15 - +91 81868 51950: Greetings from Infosys!

We are back with the fifth edition of HackWithInfy.

HackWithInfy provides the perfect stepping-stone for B.E./ B. Tech/ M.E./ M. Tech students to explore their interest in programming and an opportunity to compete and win exciting prizes. The top performers will also earn a chance to work with Infosys.


This year, *HackWithInfy is not just open to the batch of 2023, but we are also inviting participation from 2024 and 2025 batch, to prove their mettle* and win exciting cash prizes worth INR 3.5 Lakhs.


HackWithInfy competition offers ‚Äì


A chance to compete with top programmers in India
Cash prizes worth INR 350,000 to the winners
Pre-placement interview for niche technical roles at Infosys
Paid internship opportunities
Chance to become Infosys Campus Ambassador

We are thankful for all the support and collaboration you provided for HackWithInfy 2021 amid the pandemic. The competition witnessed a record breaking registrations from close to 2,00,000 students all over India.


HackWithInfy 2022 comprises two rounds -


¬∑     *Round 1- March 6,7, and 8, 2022*

An online individual participation round on the Infosys platform. Students can chose their slots on the portal, post registration. Slots will be assigned on first come, first serve basis.


They can take this assessment in either of the following languages ‚Äì

Bash, C, C++ (14), C#, Clojure, Go, Java, JavaScript, Perl, PHP, Python, Python3, R, Ruby, Swift, and TypeScript.


¬∑       *Final round: July 1 ‚Äì July 4, 2022*

In this round, the top 100 participants from Round 1 will be divided into teams for a 48-hour hackathon.


Please visit the HackWithInfy website https://www.infosys.com/careers/hackwithinfy.html
for more details.


Registrations for HackWithInfy 2022 are now open to all B.E./B. Tech/M.E./M. Tech students graduating in the years 2023, 2024, and 2025.


Steps of the registration process:

1.     *Students need to first become a registered user on InfyTQ https://infytq.onwingspan.com/en/infytq-login , our learning and engagement platform*

2.     *Once registered, go to the ‚ÄòHackWithInfy‚Äô page under the ‚ÄòPrograms‚Äô tab OR click on the HackWithInfy banner at the top of their InfyTQ homepage*

17/03/2022, 17:55 - Dhruv CBIT: Dear Students,

Smart India Hackathon 2022 (SIH-2022) is a national initiative launched by AICTE and MoE aimed at providing students with a platform to solve real-life problem statements in Government institutes and private organizations.

SIH-2022 has around 562 Problem statements which are categorized into 459 Software problems and 103 Problem statements. Winning Team will win 1 Lakh prize money and funding from corresponding organizations to push the solution into real-time usage.

SIH-2022 Problem Statements can be viewed at https://sih.gov.in/sih2022PS

As part of the SIH-2022, every college needs to send 15 Teams, which will be shortlisted through an Internal hackathon that will be conducted on 21st March, 2022 at CBIT Campus.

 *Advantages to participants* :
 _Exposure to solve real-life problems
Developed solution will be pushed to real-time usage
Working knowledge on latest technology
Exposure to hackathon culture
Development of collaboration culture among team 
Prizes and Certificates for winning teams and participants_ 

 *Who can Participate?* 
All Years and all branches of B.E/ B.Tech/M.E/ M.Tech/MCA/SMS

Register your team using below URL: https://forms.gle/h88JvJC4vkDmui8ZA

Team- SIH

03/05/2022, 18:30 - Dhruv CBIT: Dear students!

If you aspire to get placed in Software Company, please go thru the message

We have taken feedback from few of your alumni as well as current final year students who got placed and the following inputs we got from them:

*To get into 5-8 LPA job:*
1.	Coding in either C/Python/CPP - must practice on platforms like Hackerrank / CodeChef
2.	Fundamentals of Data Structures, Database Systems, Object Oriented Programming is must
3.	Must be confident in 3 to 4 program specific courses
4.	Verbal + Quant + Aptitude + Reasoning
5.	Soft Skills
6.	Company specific preparation

*To get into 8 to 25 LPA jobs:*
1.	Competitive Coding- must practice on platforms like Hackerrank / CodeChef / LeetCode
2.	Object Oriented Programming Concepts based on Java or CPP
3.	Fundamentals of Data Structures, Database Systems, Operating Systems , Software Engineering, Computer Networks - Scenario based questions not just FAQ's
4.	Full Stack Development- Must have developed an App or Web app End to End
5.	Verbal + Quant + Aptitude + Reasoning
6.	Soft Skills
7.	Company specific preparation
8.	Should be on LinkedIN with updated profile
9.	Must maintain GitHub profile
10.	Participate in minimum 2 Hackathons
11.	Atleast one Industry 4.0 certification 


*To get into >40 LPA jobs*
1.	Competitive Coding- must practice on platforms like Hackerrank / CodeChef / LeetCode
2.	Fundamentals of Data Structures, Database Systems, Operating Systems , Software Engineering, Computer Networks - Scenario based questions not just FAQ's
3.	Full Stack Development - Must have developed an App or Web app End to End
4.	Handson working experience in SpringBoot
5.	Two projects on any two emerging areas like Data Science / Artificial Intelligence / Machine Learning / IoT / Robotics / Cyber Security / Block Chain / etc‚Ä¶
6.	Verbal + Quant + Aptitude + Reasoning
7.	Soft Skills
8.	Any two Industry 4.0 approved Certifications
9.	Should be on LinkedIN with updated profile
10.	Must maintain GitHub profile
11.	Participate in minimum 2 Hackathons
12.	Publish / Presented a Paper or work on Beyond the curriculum projects

14/06/2022, 10:10 - Dhruv CBIT: AICTE has signed an MoU on 25th May, 2022 with Heartfulness Educational Trust (HET) for offering its modules and other programs to the AICTE approved institutes/colleges/universities. (The MoU can be viewed on AICTE website)

                The HET is a not-for-profit organization established with an objective of conducting programs inter alia in various universities, colleges, schools in the fields of socio-emotional learning and life skills, wellness, Leadership Mastery, capacity building amongst teachers and researchers. HET has also undertaken research in the field of response of humans to effects of meditation and to establish scientific correlation between meditation and various physiological factors associated with holistic wellness enhancement in human beings

                The details of the programs and courses (and modules) offered by the HET are as follows:

a)Elective credit based courses and/or modules for the same;
b)Foundational open elective courses for the undergraduate and post graduate students of the AICTE approved colleges/institutes/universities for holistic development of students and/or modules for the same to be part of student induction programs of AICTE approved institutions/colleges/
c)Internship opportunities to students from AICTE approved institutions.
d)Research fellowships to eligible students from AICTE approved institutions for conducting research in various fields including contemplative pedagogy, sustainable technologies, environmental sustainability, and consciousness.
e)Establishment of Heartfulness centres at AICTE approved colleges/institutes/universities for offering various tools of wellness including awareness sessions, Heartfulness meditation sessions, sharing of literature.
f)Training programme to faculty members, senior leaders, counsellors and staff from AICTE approved institutions.
                The details of courses in SCHEDULE ‚ÄúA‚Äù appended to this letter.

Further more details on HET programs may be accessed through the link https://heartfulness.org/education/heartfulcampus/ and email ID campus@heartfulness.org

                                                                                                                                                                                   Ever got fascinated with space and got engrossed in thinking, what could be behind this ever-expanding infinity? Ever considered, how to turn your fascination with this very infinity into passion? 

Chaitanya Astra is a place, an exclusive club of CBIT,  where you can put your inquisitive minds to work in order to unleash your fascination and pursue your passion for space.

We are a hands-on space enthusiast club that designs, builds, and flies a large variety of projects. Our focus is on the areas that revolve around Rocketry, Missiles, Systems Engineering, mechatronic systems and various Aerospace technologies. Our mission is to explore and unveil the next-generation space exploration technologies in an amateur, and student-driven context.
 
We welcome people from all fields of study, with or without engineering experience because We believe in the saying that ‚ÄúIf I have a belief that I can do it, I shall surely acquire the capacity, even if I might not have it at the beginning‚Äù and also because we firmly adhere that interdisciplinary approach and people (from diverse backgrounds ) are strength.

06/10/2022, 21:03 - +91 90143 79255: Greetings from team Computer Society of India (CSI), the student branch chapter of VNR VJIET.

We, the members of CSI VNR VJIET, are conducting VJ Hackathon 2022 (Victory & Joy in Smart Innovations) in collaboration with the Department of Computer Science & Engineering. VJ Hackathon 2022 will be held on *4th & 5th November, 2022*. It is a nationwide event with participants and jurors coming from all over the country including IITs, NITs, IIITs and other Universities. 
 
The *domains* under the hackathon include:
1. Agriculture
2. Smart Education
3. Healthcare
 
*Hackathon Process :*
‚Ä¢ Select a problem statement from the attached document.
‚Ä¢ Upload a PPT in the registration form given, once you‚Äôve come up with a possible solution, on or before *15th October, 2022*
‚Ä¢ Teams will be shortlisted based on your PPT and the results will be updated on *22nd October, 2022*.
 
Team size: maximum 3 students, 1 mentor (optional)
 
Cash Prizes include:
Winner: Rs 10,000 (for each Domain)
Runner: Rs 7,000 (for each Domain)
 
Registration link:
https://forms.gle/3EXtVzWdt5UAiy7t9

The drive link to access the problem statements, instructions document and sample ppt is below :
https://bit.ly/3R5EreV

Participation certificates for the participants and winner certificates for the finalists will be given. 

 
Note:
1. Participants are requested to travel to VNR VJIET, Hyderabad, Telangana on their own. Accommodation for one night will be provided.
2. There is no registration fee for the first round. The teams shortlisted for finals will be requested to pay Rs. 500 (per team) for accommodation on November 4th, 2022.
3. Lunch, Dinner and Breakfast will be provided in two days.
4. Participants are requested to stay within the campus on both the days.
5. Goodies will be given to the shortlisted teams.
6. *The organizers are not responsible for any action taken as a consequence of violation of rules.*

Boeing in Partnership with T-Hub is looking for applications from young entrepreneurial minds to develop ideas that can be converted into viable business offerings. Interested applicants are invited to submit ideas that can help solve real-world challenges in the fields of :

01. Mobility

07. Data Analytics / AI

Accredited by NBA & NAAC.

We're hosting an AICTE Sponsored *6th INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE* on *Intelligent Computing and Communication (ICICC 2022)*  on *18th & 19th  of November 2022* 

Jointly Organised by *Department of CSE, GNITS and NITW*.

On this occasion CSE Department is arranging a *Pre-Conference Workshop* on the topic 
‚Äú *_Architecting Application Lifecycle Automation using DevOps_*"

*Programme Deliverables*
This workshop enables participants to understand the Human skills needed in this Digital Transformation era specific to Application Lifecycle Automation using DevOps Process and Tools.

Participants will be walking through a complete Application Lifecycle Automation demo using popular Commercial and Open-Source DevOps Tools to perform a Zero Touch CI/CD Process.

*Who should attend:* Faculty, Research Scholars, Students from Academic institutions can attend the pre-conference workshop

17/11/2022, 16:44 - Dhruv CBIT: Twitter is in the headlines for multiple controversies but did you know Twitter was built in a hackathon? 
Likewise, Zapier, Carousel, Easy Taxi, and many internal Meta(Previously Facebook) features were some of the innovations that took place in hackathons and created billions of dollars of value. 
Hence, we believe hackathons are the best place to build future innovators as it provides you with the right exposure and challenging environment to tap into your highest potential. 

We, the *Department of Computer Science and Engineering* of *Vasavi College of Engineering(Autonomous)* bring to you the first-of-its-kind Hybrid Hackathon spanning 24 hours, *"Innovasia 2022"* specially focused on upholding the spirit of innovation. 

The hackathon has 2 rounds. All the participants will have to submit the idea by 21st November 2022 6:00 PM IST. Based on the ideas submitted,  top teams will be selected and will be invited to Vasavi College of Engineering for Round 2.

Please note that the shortlisted teams have to pay the registration fee of *Rs. 400/-* per team by *27th November 2022*

 The second round will commence on 2nd December 2022 at 7:00 AM IST for all the shortlisted teams in online mode followed by an offline mode hackathon on 3rd December 2022 from 7:00 AM IST. Lunch and snacks for all the shortlisted teams will be provided at the Venue on 3rd December 2022. Please note that teams will be evaluated on a rolling basis as we have limited slots.

We came up with problems that we believe require much innovation. The problem statements for INNOVASIA 2022 are:

*Education*: Come up with Smart assessment systems to evaluate students and identify the learning gaps well.

*Health*: Come up with innovative applications to make subsidized healthcare transparent and efficient

*AgriTech*: Come up with innovative solutions to impact the agriculture industry by leveraging any applicable technologies.

We hope this hackathon helps you unleash the innovator in you. This hackathon will also provide you with abundant networking opportunities that would propel your innovation journey forward. Through this effort, we want to celebrate the innovators in you and nurture your visionary ideas to push the humanity forward. 

Registration link: https://bit.ly/innovasia-vce

Visit our website for more information: 
https://innovasia-vce.devpost.com

For any additional queries, please contact the student coordinators 

*Sharat Chandra - 9059726556*

*Akash Vora - 79812 89964*

*innovasia@vce.ac.in*
